ChangeLog: V7.3 Changelog -> Added Distance slider and Targeting Mode dropdown to Moves Aimbot with "Angle & Distance" and "Distance" options, improving enemy prioritization while fighting. -> Added Targeting Mode dropdown and Distance slider to TP Behind Moves. -> Lock On is now a toggle; body part selection updates instantly without resetting the lock, along with additional improvements. -> Added Smooth Lock toggle in the Lock On section. -> Replaced the old Quests ESP toggle with an NPCs ESP dropdown featuring "Pending Quests", "No Quest", and "All". -> Added Cell Jr, Android 19, and Android 20 quests to Auto Quest. -> Added a Media section to the Misc page. -> Added Acrylic Blur in UI Settings to improve text readability and modernize the interface. -> Added new UI themes: Amberfall, Neon Tide, Verdant Glass, Midnight Prism, Frozen Aurora, and Opaline Halo. -> Added a secondary fallback source to improve script loading reliability if the primary request fails. -> Themes now load significantly faster. -> Several buttons are now bindable (Earth TP, Namek TP, Lobby TP, Fling, UnHook, Invite Everyone, Load Configuration, Load Race Configuration), along with additional toggles. -> Auto Quest now automatically drinks Korin Water. -> Slightly increased nearby enemy detection radius at boss doors in Auto Dungeon. -> Adjusted minimum and default values in Hide Distance; Hide From Players now travels slightly faster initially. -> Spy Chat is now disabled by default to reduce accidental exposure. -> Improved HTTP error notifications for clearer load failure diagnostics. -> Various internal UI improvements and notification system cleanup. -> Patched an important on-execution detection related to the UI library (never detected). -> Patched a potential Lock On detection (never detected). -> Fixed an issue where loading configurations removed feature descriptions. -> Fixed Auto Quest selecting the wrong option for the EcosystemGiver quest on first completion. -> Fixed an error when the UI Library failed to load. -> Fixed an issue in the Players Health Bar feature. -> Other minor fixes and stability improvements (e.g., UnHook disabling UI customization toggles).
